Teltoli notcied Carnage shiver slightly, and she made a note to ask 
Carnage about her own past.. unless she didn't want to talk about it.

She then giggled at the special additives comment. "I reckon - 
Cybertronian food did taste kinda fake.. but it served. But at leats 
we didn't have to eat MRE's every day in the army! Disgusting things. 
They all tasted the same.. even if they were labeled to be different 
flavours"

The Fuzor drew slightly back at Carnage's question. What was it like 
to be loved by a family? Wow.. she had never been asked something 
like that before, and had never really thought about it either.

"Uh.. I guess it's.. nice?" She offered lamely, then shoek her head 
at her own patheticness. "Sorry, it's kinda a difficult question. 
Well, it was nice, to be loved, I mean. To know that your Father and 
Mother were there when you got home from hanging out with your 
friends. Knowing they'll support you wherever you go.."

Her eyes glazed over, and she stayed silent for a few seconds, arms 
to crossed across her chest. "But you can get in big fights. I got in 
a few with my Dad.. but never my Mum" She shrugged.

"As I said.. it's nice" She grinned.
